response.original_title: Joseph and the Amazing Technicolor Dreamcoat
response.overview: Joseph, the favored son of Jacob, is betrayed by his jealous brothers, sold into slavery, and driven to Egypt. Though beset with adversity, Joseph perseveres through wit and faith and becomes the Governor of Egypt, second only to the Pharaoh.
response.tagline: Tim Rice & Andrew Lloyd Webber's Classic Family Musical
